ilda

Class IldaPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • ilda.IldaPoint

  • public class IldaPoint
extends java.lang.Object
    A point of an ilda frame. Location is stored in three floats (xyz) ranging from -1 to 1. Colour is stored in an integer which is a 32 bit number: the first eight bits are not used, the second eight bits are red (0-255), the next eight represent green and the last eight bits are blue. This corresponds to a "color" data type in Processing. This is the "official" colour representation: points also store a palIndex but this is only used to set the colour of a palette, never to render it to a screen. A point also has a blanked flag which determines if the point is off or on.
